Project description

The Gurobi Optimizer is a mathematical optimization software libraryfor solving mixed-integer linear and quadratic optimization problems.

This package comes with a trial license that allows you to solveproblems of limited size. As a student or staff member of an academicinstitution you qualify for a free, full product license. Formore information, see:

  • https://www.gurobi.com/academia/academic-program-and-licenses/

For a commercial evaluation, you can request an evaluation license.

Other useful resources to get started:

  • https://www.gurobi.com/documentation/

  • https://support.gurobi.com/hc/en-us/community/topics

A simple example

# Solve the following MIP:#  maximize#        x +   y + 2 z#  subject to#        x + 2 y + 3 z <= 4#        x +   y       >= 1#        x, y, z binaryimport gurobipy as gp# Create a new modelm = gp.Model()# Create variablesx = m.addVar(vtype='B', name="x")y = m.addVar(vtype='B', name="y")z = m.addVar(vtype='B', name="z")# Set objective functionm.setObjective(x + y + 2 * z, gp.GRB.MAXIMIZE)# Add constraintsm.addConstr(x + 2 * y + 3 * z <= 4)m.addConstr(x + y >= 1)# Solve it!m.optimize()print(f"Optimal objective value: {m.objVal}")print(f"Solution values: x={x.X}, y={y.X}, z={z.X}")
